葉山港から相模湾を隔てて、富士山と江ノ島を眺める。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kanagawa" /><category term="Mt. Fuji" /><category term="Water" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking across Sagami Bay at Mt. Fuji and Enoshima Island, from Hayama Harbor. 葉山港から相模湾を隔てて、富士山と江ノ島を眺める。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_IMG_3777_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_IMG_3777_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">River Boats・屋形船</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260520/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="River Boats・屋形船" /><published>2026-05-20T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-20T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/boats</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260520/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Many boats on the Katsura River in Arashiyama on a warm, sunny day.
</p>
<p class="jp">
暖かく晴れた日、嵐山の桂川には多くの屋形船が浮かんでいる。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Boats" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Many boats on the Katsura River in Arashiyama on a warm, sunny day. 暖かく晴れた日、嵐山の桂川には多くの屋形船が浮かんでいる。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01654.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01654.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Morning in the Grove・竹林の朝</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260519/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Morning in the Grove・竹林の朝" /><published>2026-05-19T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-19T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/grove</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260519/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A walk in the soft morning light of Arashiyama's Bamboo Grove.
</p>
<p class="jp">
嵐山の竹林を、柔らかな朝の日差しの中を散歩した。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Bamboo Grove" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A walk in the soft morning light of Arashiyama's Bamboo Grove. 嵐山の竹林を、柔らかな朝の日差しの中を散歩した。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01616_edit-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01616_edit-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kyoto Station・京都駅</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260515/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kyoto Station・京都駅" /><published>2026-05-15T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-15T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kyoto-station</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260515/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
One of the long escalators at Kyoto Station, shot from the Skyway at the very top of the large station building.
</p>
<p class="jp">
京都駅の長いエスカレーターの一つ。巨大な駅舎の最上階にあるスカイウェイから撮影した。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[One of the long escalators at Kyoto Station, shot from the Skyway at the very top of the large station building. 京都駅の長いエスカレーターの一つ。巨大な駅舎の最上階にあるスカイウェイから撮影した。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01580_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01580_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Tohka Saikan・東華菜館</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260511/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tohka Saikan・東華菜館" /><published>2026-05-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tohkasaikan</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260511/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The historic Tohka Saikan Chinese restaurant (1924) and the Shijo Ohashi bridge over the Kamogawa river, in a long exposure at dusk.
</p>
<p class="jp">
大正13年建築の由緒ある中華料理店「東華菜館」と、鴨川に架かる四条大橋を、夕暮れ時の長時間露光で捉えた写真だ。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Bridges" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Long Exposure" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The historic Tohka Saikan Chinese restaurant (1924) and the Shijo Ohashi bridge over the Kamogawa river, in a long exposure at dusk. 大正13年建築の由緒ある中華料理店「東華菜館」と、鴨川に架かる四条大橋を、夕暮れ時の長時間露光で捉えた写真だ。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSCF1821_edit_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSCF1821_edit_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Morning on the Togetsu Bridge・渡月橋の朝</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260509/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Morning on the Togetsu Bridge・渡月橋の朝" /><published>2026-05-09T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-09T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/togetsukyo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260509/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Stopping to take a picture of the beautiful view in Arashiyama this morning. Me too.
</p>
<p class="jp">
今朝、嵐山で美しい景色を写真に収めるために足を止めた。私も。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><category term="Views" /><category term="Clouds" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Stopping to take a picture of the beautiful view in Arashiyama this morning. Me too. 今朝、嵐山で美しい景色を写真に収めるために足を止めた。私も。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01543.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01543.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">So Green・とても緑豊か</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260507/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="So Green・とても緑豊か" /><published>2026-05-07T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-07T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/green</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260507/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Verdant green mountains in Arashiyama, south of the Katsura River. So green, I had to turn down the color saturation to make it believable.😉
</p>
<p class="jp">
桂川の南側にある嵐山の、青々とした緑の山々。あまりにも緑が鮮やかだったので、信じてもらえるように彩度を下げざるを得なかった。😉
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><category term="Panoramas" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Verdant green mountains in Arashiyama, south of the Katsura River. So green, I had to turn down the color saturation to make it believable.😉 桂川の南側にある嵐山の、青々とした緑の山々。あまりにも緑が鮮やかだったので、信じてもらえるように彩度を下げざるを得なかった。😉]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2713-Pano.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2713-Pano.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Enjoying the Day・一日を楽しむ</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260505/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Enjoying the Day・一日を楽しむ" /><published>2026-05-05T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-05T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260505/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Three friends sit on a bench overlooking the Togetsukyo bridge, on a sunny spring day.
</p>
<p class="jp">
